ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE POLICIES

 The Mobil Chemical Company Polyethylene Plant (PE plant) in Beaumont, Texas produces both low density and high density polyethylene using a variety of chemicals and processing operations.  Our polyethylene pellets are used to make a wide variety of plastic products.  The PE plant utilizes certain safety precautions to prevent unnecessary on site human exposure and to minimize the potential for any off site exposure.  These safety precautions include:

	o  Effectively managing our process operations;
	o  Investing in the latest process safety technologies;
	o  Training our personnel on an ongoing basis;
	o  Reviewing our processes for hazards on a continuous basis;
	o  Ensuring safety is considered in process design, installation, operations and maintenance;
	o Training and maintaining a highly efficient emergency response organization.

The PE plant maintains a policy to be a good business partner and a safe and conscientious neighbor; who wll operate its facility in compliance with all applicable laws and regulations.  

The PE plant has a standing commitment to worker and public safety.  This is evidenced by:

	o  our history of support and commitment to the community;
	o  our high environmental standards;
	o  our participation as a STAR facility in the U.S. Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) Voluntary Protection Program (VPP) since 1984.

We are proud of our Safety and Environmental programs and contine to strive to be the best in our industry.



DESCRIPTION OF THE STATIONARY SOURCE AND REGULATED SUBSTANCES

The manufacturing process at the PE plant contains the RMP regulated flammable substances of butene, ethylene, hydrogen, isopentane, and propylene. In addition, the PE plant uses vinyl acetate, which is a regulated toxic substance under the RMP rule, as a process additive.

